data.event: A group of English and Scottish colonists led by a Scotsman named George Grant founded Victoria in 1873 on land he had purchased from the Kansas Pacific Railway.

event.title: 1876, Volga Germans from villages near Saratov, Russia established

data.event: In 1876, Volga Germans from villages near Saratov, Russia established the settlement of Herzog one half mile north of Victoria.

event.title: known as "The Cathedral of the Plains," in 1911

data.event: Herzog's Roman Catholic settlers built a series of churches which culminated in the construction of St. Fidelis Catholic Church, known as "The Cathedral of the Plains," in 1911.
Herzog was officially renamed Victoria in 1913.
